		<title>04ARABLE FARMING (2),KIRKCALDY</title>
		<content> Differences in the emphasis between   
 farms in the area can be illustrated  
 by comparing Banchory and Craigencalt 
 farms.                                
                                       
{1.BANCHORY FARM} (430 ACRES)          
        barley (and some wheat)...75%  
                       potatoes...10%  
                          grass...10%  
                        turnips....5%  
                                       
{2.CRAIGENCALT FARM }(256 ACRES)       
                          grass...75%  
                         barley...25%  
                                       
 The larger part of Craigencalt is     
 situated on the steeper ground above  
 Kinghorn Loch, making it more         
 difficult to sow and harvest crops,   
 and hence economically more suitable  
 for livestock farming.                
                                       </content>
